I don‚Äôt think I‚Äôve ever seen another film that‚Äôs replicated the sheer ugliness of Chesty Morgan-era 70s sexploitation as well as VIVA. The points of reference are pretty clear - it‚Äôs essentially a who‚Äôs who of the Something Weird Video catalog - but, I think that focusing on the fact that, say, one sequence looks like something from a Metzger film is the wrong approach to take. It‚Äôs obvious that Anna Biller has a real understanding of the underlying sexism of even the most ‚Äòpro-woman‚Äô of sexploitation films (and, really, the sexual revolution as a whole) and is using the trappings of the genre - nudist camps, eccentric artists, orgies, suburban melodrama, etc - to subvert and comment on it. The film runs a little long, but that's not much of a criticism. It's a tour- de-force in every respect and a pretty astonishing and fearless debut feature. Loved it.
